Hi!

I have the following models:

```python
class Parent(Document):
    child = ReferenceField('Child')


class Child(Document):
    text = StringField(primary_key=True)
```

An `OPTIONS` request on the `Parent` endpoint in the browsable API displays something like:

```
// ...
"child": {
    "type": "field",
    "required": true,
    "read_only": false,
    "label": "Type",
    "choices": [
        {
            "value": "word",
            "display_name": "USLType object"
        }
    ]
}
// ...
```

But when I send this `POST` request:

```
{
    "child": "word"
}
```

I obtain the error:

```
{
    "child": [
        "Cannot parse \"text1\" as ObjectIdField."
    ]
}
```

If I send the request with the id of the `Child`:

```
{
    "child": "5947f817561e3ad0aacfc6be"
}
```

I obtain the Django error:

```
LookUpError at /library/usls/

Cannot resolve field "id"
```

Thanks

**Edit :** explanations [here](https://github.com/umutbozkurt/django-rest-framework-mongoengine/blob/2067a702837a2387c7c1c01b2d296b44a53d25b5/rest_framework_mongoengine/fields.py#L211).

The bifurcation angle is defined as the angle between the lines connecting a parent point to its two child points in a morphology. We explicitly exclude multifurcations beyond two. Many biological cells have artifacts in which one or both children are at zero distance from their parent. We do not want to reject these points in calculating the bifurcation angles as they often constitute a large subset of any neuron's bifurcation points.

A simple solution is to make a check when calculating a bifurcation angle:

if( both children are greater than epsilon from their parent)
    calculate bifurcation angle using the two vectors from parent to the children
else if( one or both children are less than epsilon from their parent)
    replace the child of zero length with its own child if it is unique; if one child is itself a bifurcation ignore it.

    if( both these children exist)
       calculate the bifurcation angle using these children/grandchildren
    else
       // one child must be a termination
       do not count this point as a bifurcation

