I'm invoking Duality through the (OCaml) API, but I can't find one of the API functions that I need.

In SMT-LIBv2, we can register our relations and the universally quantified variables using `(declare-rel A)` and `(declare-var x)` respectively. I see `Z3_fixedpoint_register_relation` in `src/api/api_datalog.cpp`, and it is exposed in OCaml as `register_relation` in `src/api/ml/z3.mli`.

However I cannot find a corresponding `Z3_fixedpoint_register_variable` in the API. I tried to write my own. Is this right?
```
void Z3_API Z3_fixedpoint_register_variable(Z3_context c, Z3_fixedpoint d, Z3_func_decl f) {
    Z3_TRY;
    to_fixedpoint_ref(d)->ctx().register_variable(to_func_decl(f));
